🔹 **Metoclopramide**: D2 + 5-HT4. Crosses BBB → EPS risk. Max 12 weeks use

🔹 **Domperidone**: D2 antagonist. No BBB crossing → No EPS. Cardiac risk (QT)

🔹 **Erythromycin**: Motilin agonist. Effective but tachyphylaxis develops quickly

🔹 **Uses**: Gastroparesis, GERD, post-op ileus, feeding intolerance

🔹 **Contraindications**: Mechanical obstruction, GI bleeding, perforation`,
