  {
    id: 'ibd-drugs',
    subjectId: 'pharmacology',
    subspecialtyId: 'pharmacology-gi',
    name: 'IBD Drugs',
    slug: 'ibd-drugs',
    description: '5-ASA, corticosteroids, azathioprine, biologics, Crohn vs UC treatment',
    content: {
      concept: `# Inflammatory Bowel Disease Drugs

## IBD Overview

**Two main forms:**
- **Ulcerative Colitis (UC)**: Colonic mucosal inflammation
- **Crohn's Disease (CD)**: Transmural, any GI location

## Drug Classification

| Class | Examples | Mechanism | Use |
|-------|----------|-----------|-----|
| **Aminosalicylates** | 5-ASA, Sulfasalazine | Anti-inflammatory | Induction/Maintenance |
| **Corticosteroids** | Prednisolone, Budesonide | Anti-inflammatory/Immunosuppressive | Induction only |
| **Immunomodulators** | Azathioprine, Methotrexate | T-cell suppression | Maintenance/Steroid-sparing |
| **Anti-TNF biologics** | Infliximab, Adalimumab | TNF-α neutralization | Moderate-severe disease |
| **Other biologics** | Vedolizumab, Ustekinumab | Selective targets | Anti-TNF failures |

[Content continues with detailed sections on each drug class...]`,
      keyPoints: [
        '5-ASA drugs are first-line for mild-moderate UC; topical forms for distal disease',
        'Corticosteroids for induction only; not for maintenance due to side effects',
        'Azathioprine requires TPMT testing; 6-MP is active metabolite',
        'Anti-TNF biologics (infliximab, adalimumab) for moderate-severe IBD',
        'Budesonide has fewer systemic effects than prednisolone',
        'Vedolizumab is gut-selective integrin inhibitor',
        'Treatment differs between UC (mainly colon) and CD (any location)'
      ],
      examPrep: {
        summary: `**IBD Drugs - Quick Review**

🔹 **5-ASA**: First-line UC. Sulfasalazine (cheap), Mesalazine (better tolerated)

🔹 **Corticosteroids**: Induction only. Budesonide (↓ systemic effects)

🔹 **Immunomodulators**: Azathioprine (TPMT test), MTX (Crohn's)

🔹 **Anti-TNF**: Infliximab, Adalimumab. Moderate-severe disease

🔹 **Gut-selective**: Vedolizumab (integrin), Budesonide (steroid)`,
